Overview-

This defined pattern is for the Exception Cature and Incident logging process which was followed in SAP BTP Integration Suite to integrate SAP and NON- SAP Applications.

Please refer to HLD and IDD documents for actual implementation integration flow of the interface.

Asynchronous outbound flow covers the entire failure of the integration and record the exception based on the type in database or datastore.

Excetions in the flow are classified into 

1. Application Exceptions:
These could be due to backend system outages or connectivity
issues or any other issue which would keep occurring even if the application
message is changed. e.g., Backend service is unavailable (http status code
503), Conection Timeout.

Exception saved in Database and Data Store.

2. Business Exceptions:
These are due to message data problems which could be wrong data

type, missing data, or any other data related issue. This would be fixed by the
source system. e.g., Bad Request (http status code 400),

Exception saved in Database.
